XVI.

12. quod is the reading of some inferior MSS.; que V; qui (quei) Ellis from a few MSS. With qui I think a subjunctive would have been required. There is little to be said for quom, L. Mtiller.

XXI.

11. me me puer MSS.; Mellitus Hand, followed by Ellis. Scaliger’s a! me me, accepted by Mliller, is palaeographically tempting; but the repetition os me is tame. Faernus, with some probability, conjectured, vae ! meur.
